#: ../../M/manularity.rst:5
msgid "manularity"
msgstr "manularity"

#: ../../M/manularity.rst:7
msgid "/man\\`yoo·la´ri·tee/, n\\."
msgstr "/man\\`yoo·la´ri·tee/, 名詞"

#: ../../M/manularity.rst:9
msgid ""
"[prob. fr. techspeak manual + granularity] A notional measure of the manual "
"labor required for some task, particularly one of the sort that automation "
"is supposed to eliminate. \"Composing English on paper has much higher "
"manularity than using a text editor, especially in the revising stage.\" "
"Hackers tend to consider manularity a symptom of primitive methods; in fact,"
" a true hacker confronted with an apparent requirement to do a computing "
"task :ref:`by-hand` will inevitably seize the opportunity to build another "
"tool (see :ref:`toolsmith`\\)."
msgstr ""
"[おそらくtechspeakのmanual + "
"granularityから]ある作業、特に自動化が排除するはずの種類の作業に必要な手作業の量の概念的な尺度。「紙の上で英語を作文することは、特に推敲段階で、テキストエディタを使うよりはるかに高いmanularityを持つ」。ハッカーはmanularityを原始的な手法の症状と見なす傾向がある。実際、真のハッカーは計算作業を\\"
" :ref:`by-hand`\\ で行うという明らかな要求に直面すると、必ずや別の道具を作る機会をつかむ(\\ :ref:`toolsmith`\\ "
"を参照)。"
